ğŸ§  What is Context API?

Context API is a way to **share data globally** in a React app **without passing props manually at every level**.

ğŸ“Œ Introduced in React 16.3
ğŸ“Œ Used for global state management

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ What is Prop Drilling?

Prop drilling happens when you pass data through many components unnecessarily.

### Example:

```
App
 â””â”€â”€ Parent
      â””â”€â”€ Child
           â””â”€â”€ GrandChild
```

If GrandChild needs data from App â†’
You must pass props through Parent and Child ğŸ˜“

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âœ… Solution: Context API

Context allows you to:

* Store data globally
* Access it anywhere
* Avoid prop drilling

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 1: Create Context

```jsx
import { createContext } from "react";

const MyContext = createContext();
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 2: Provide Context

Wrap your components inside Provider.

```jsx
<MyContext.Provider value="Hello Context">
  <Child />
</MyContext.Provider>
```

ğŸ“Œ `value` is the data shared

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 3: Consume Context (useContext Hook)

```jsx
import { useContext } from "react";

function Child() {
  const value = useContext(MyContext);
  return <h2>{value}</h2>;
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Now Child gets data directly

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Complete Example

```jsx
import React, { createContext, useContext } from "react";

const UserContext = createContext();

function App() {
  return (
    <UserContext.Provider value="Saakshi">
      <Profile />
    </UserContext.Provider>
  );
}

function Profile() {
  const user = useContext(UserContext);
  return <h2>Welcome {user}</h2>;
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Context with State (More Practical)

```jsx
const ThemeContext = createContext();

function App() {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState("light");

  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={{ theme, setTheme }}>
      <Home />
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}
```

Access:

```jsx
const { theme, setTheme } = useContext(ThemeContext);
```

ğŸ“Œ Can update global state

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  When to Use Context API?

âœ” Authentication data
âœ” Theme (dark/light mode)
âœ” User info
âœ” Language settings
âœ” App settings

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ When NOT to Use Context

âŒ Frequently changing data (performance issues)
âŒ Very large global state
âŒ Complex state management

For complex apps â†’ Use Redux / Zustand

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š Context API vs Props

| Props               | Context              |
| ------------------- | -------------------- |
| Passed manually     | Global access        |
| Good for small apps | Good for shared data |
| Clear data flow     | Avoids prop drilling |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Context API vs Redux (Basic Difference)

| Context API         | Redux                    |
| ------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Built-in React      | External library         |
| Simple global state | Complex state management |
| Small-medium apps   | Large-scale apps         |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Common Mistakes

âŒ Overusing context
âŒ Forgetting Provider
âŒ Creating context inside component
âŒ Not memoizing value

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ” Keep context small
âœ” Split multiple contexts if needed
âœ” Use custom hooks for cleaner code
âœ” Wrap app at top level

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Custom Hook for Cleaner Context Usage

```jsx
function useUser() {
  return useContext(UserContext);
}
```

Usage:

```jsx
const user = useUser();
```

âœ” Cleaner
âœ” Reusable

